49
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
 in Calcutta, India.

50
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,000
 This is what she said of the vulnerable people that she encountered

51
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,000
 amidst her own struggles and doubts about her faith.

52
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:49,000
 Her life's work, no matter how poor or destitute those she worked with were,

53
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:55,000
 was to see them as they truly are, as blessed children bearing God's image

54
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
 no matter where they've come from or who they are.

55
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:03,000
 Brandon Heath, a contemporary Christian artist known for at least two hits,

56
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
 "Give Me Your Eyes" and "The Light in Me,"

57
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:13,000
 was moved by Mother Teresa's words to write a song in 2008 called "Jesus in Disguise."

58
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:19,000
