59
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
 it's not about ministry these days.

60
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
 It's about fear.

61
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,000
 Fear of people who have been displaced.

62
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:31,000
 They are labeled as a haven for terrorists who are intent on harming us

63
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:35,000
 but disguising themselves to sneak into our country.

64
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:40,000
 In light of 9/11 this weekend, I can certainly see our reasons for caution here.

65
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,000
 But a couple things I think that we should know,

66
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:49,000
 and that is that it's not likely that our country would have that happen through those we serve.

67
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:56,000
 Our country's track record on refugee resettlement is a strong and stable work.

68
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:03,000
 Three million people have actually been brought into this country over the past 30, 40 years now,

69
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:09,000
 since 1980 with the Refugee Act, and not one citizen has died at the hands of a refugee.

70
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:14,000
 So that vetting process has been pretty thorough and extensive through the years.

71
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:22,000
 Inciting fear of certain people in blanket ways to cast blame on them is bigotry and racism,

72
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:28,000
 and it should not be tolerated and should not happen, especially among those of us that are Christians.

73
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 Our country and its leaders have not always gotten that right either, and for that I do apologize.

74
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:39,000
 This is not an easy topic, though, I want to say to you to discuss,

75
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:43,000
 so I pray that you hear what I say in the right spirit.

76
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:50,000
 Just as it is the government's responsibility to properly vet people that are entering this country,

77
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:54,000
 it is the Christian's responsibility to welcome the stranger.

78
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:58,000
 If we expect the government to do their job, then we should do ours.

79
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:06,000
 Most of us who identify as Christians have never really thought about migration or forced migration in particular,

80
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:10,000
 but it's in the Bible. From its beginning, in the book of Genesis,

81
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:17,000
 we find a man and a woman violating the laws of the land and placed in removal from the Garden of Eden,

82
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:24,000
 which is forced displacement. At the end of the Bible, we find John writing the book of Revelation in Patmos,

83
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:28,000
 where he is exiled as an expatriate for his beliefs.

84
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:34,000
 The Bible is full of story after story of forcibly displaced people.

85
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:38,000
 Joseph was forcibly displaced as a victim of human trafficking.

86
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:43,000
 Moses was forcibly displaced for taking justice in his own hands.

87
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:54,000
 Moses certainly carried that out. David was forcibly displaced as a political refugee on the run from King Saul for 12 years of his life.

88
00:06:54,000 --> 00:07:05,000
 And Jesus was forcibly displaced to Egypt with his family soon after his birth to find safety from profiling and ethnic cleansing as a refugee.

89
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:12,000
 And the first missionary in the Bible, if we think of it this way, Philip ran from Samaria or ran to Samaria

90
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:17,000
 because of religious persecution that had broken out in the city of Jerusalem.

91
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:23,000
 Priscilla and Aquila, who were Paul's business partners and ministry partners together,

92
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:28,000
 were forcibly displaced to leave Rome and go to Corinth because of their beliefs.

93
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:34,000
 That's how Paul met them, is because Caesar had thrown out all of the Jews from Rome.

94
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:43,000
 Forced displacement is in the Bible, but very few Christians have recognized it or understood what it means for us and how we treat them.

95
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:52,000
 World Relief for Us has a 40-day Bible reading and prayer challenge just to help churches understand more of our responsibilities in this area

96
